---
const pageTitle = "Individuation";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        --paper: #ffffff;
        --ink: #000000;
        --line: #000000;
        --soft: #efefef;
        --blue: #0000ee;
        --red: #cc0000;
        --green: #008000;
      }

      html, body {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      a { text-decoration: underline; }
      a.blue { color: var(--blue); }
      a.red { color: var(--red); }
      a.green { color: var(--green); }

      .page {
        width: min(900px, calc(100% - 48px));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 28px 0 60px;
      }

      .topbar {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 10px 14px;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
        text-align: center;
        background: #fafafa;
      }

      .frame {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 22px 24px 28px;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 40px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 0 0 8px;
      }

      .subtitle {
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 16px;
        margin-bottom: 24px;
      }

      .divider {
        text-align: center;
        margin: 18px 0 24px;
      }

      p { margin-bottom: 16px; }

      .quote {
        margin: 22px auto;
        max-width: 680px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 14px;
        background: var(--soft);
        font-style: italic;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .section-title {
        font-size: 28px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 34px 0 16px;
      }

      .mini-links {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 30px;
      }

      .mini-links a {
        margin: 0 10px;
      }

      .footer-note {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 26px;
        font-size: 14px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="page">
      <div class="topbar">
        [ <a class="blue" href="/">home</a> ]
        [ <a class="blue" href="/foundations">foundations index</a> ]
        [ <a class="green" href="/foundations/conscious-and-unconscious">previous</a> ]
        [ <a class="red" href="/foundations/shadow-projection">next</a> ]
      </div>

      <main class="frame">
        <h1>Individuation</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">foundations / inner process / archive entry 002</p>

        <div class="divider">***</div>

        <p>
          Individuation is the process of becoming who you actually are.
        </p>

        <p>
          Not who you were told to be. Not who you learned to imitate. Not the version of yourself built to survive or be accepted. Individuation is the slow uncovering of the deeper pattern within you.
        </p>

        <div class="quote">
          Individuation is not self improvement. It is self realization.
        </div>

        <p>
          It begins when the life you are living starts to feel incomplete, false, or disconnected. Something feels off, even if everything looks fine on the outside.
        </p>

        <h2 class="section-title">the false self</h2>

        <p>
          Most people begin life by adapting. You learn how to act, what to say, what is rewarded, what is rejected. Over time this becomes your <a class="blue" href="/foundations/what-is-the-self">identity</a>.
        </p>

        <p>
          But this identity is often only partial. It leaves out parts of you that were inconvenient, painful, or unacceptable.
        </p>

        <p>
          Those hidden parts do not disappear. They wait.
        </p>

        <h2 class="section-title">the turning point</h2>

        <p>
          At some point, life begins to push back. This can come as anxiety, confusion, depression, loss, or a sense of emptiness.
        </p>

        <p>
          It feels like something is breaking. But something is actually trying to emerge.
        </p>

        <div class="quote">
          What feels like collapse is often the beginning of alignment.
        </div>

        <h2 class="section-title">integration</h2>

        <p>
          Individuation requires facing what has been avoided. This includes fear, shame, anger, desire, and contradiction.
        </p>

        <p>
          The goal is not to remove these things. The goal is to relate to them consciously.
        </p>

        <p>
          This is where the <a class="red" href="/dreams/shadow-projection">shadow</a> becomes important.
        </p>

        <h2 class="section-title">a lifelong process</h2>

        <p>
          Individuation does not end. There is no final version of you that is complete.
        </p>

        <p>
          It is a continuous process of becoming more aware, more real, and more whole.
        </p>

        <p>
          The more you align with your inner pattern, the more your life begins to feel like your own.
        </p>

        <div class="mini-links">
          <a class="blue" href="/foundations">back to foundations index</a>
          <a class="blue" href="/foundations/shadow-projection">continue to: shadow projection</a>
          <a class="red" href="/dreams/active-imagination">active imagination</a>
          <a class="green" href="/self/creativity-and-fantasy">creativity</a>
        </div>

        <p class="footer-note">this page is part of the hidden archive.</p>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>